     WHAT IS SPF?
     ────────────

       A mathematical framework that teaches AI
     systems to self-govern —
       dynamically adjusting how much to THINK
     versus how much to OUTPUT
       based on task complexity.

       AI systems fail on complex tasks not from
     lack of capability,
       but from lack of self-regulation. SPF fixes
      that.


     ═════════════════════════════════════════════
     ══════════════════════════════════
          THE ALGORITHM  -  BASE OF CODE
     ═════════════════════════════════════════════
     ═════════════════════════════════════════════
     ══════════════════════════════════


     STEP 1: CALCULATE COMPLEXITY
     ────────────────────────────

       STAGE 1  DETERMINE ALLOCATION OF  C = ( analysis ( complexity determines % )+ process completion )

       ANALYZE REQUIRED ALLOCATION LEVEL OF C = use 80% total available                      
       processing power. To determine allocation and value of C 

       C = (total processing power available) =
       ( (analyze = required amount of total processing power to complete task successfully ) 
       + ( process = amount of total prcessing power allocated to processing and completing tasks. remainder or 80% total ) 


     STEP 2: PROCESS BUILD USING STAGE 1 ALLOCATION CALCULATION           ────────────────────────────

       ┌────────────────────────┬─────────────────
     ┬─────────────────┐
       │ TASK TYPE              │ ANALYZE
     │ BUILD           │
       ├────────────────────────┼─────────────────
     ┼─────────────────┤
       │ Simple process       (C < 500)   │ ~40%
       | No analysis ( simple cmds )
     │ ~60%            │
       │ Simple process       (C < 2000) │ ~60%
       | Low analysis 
     │ ~40%            │
       │ Medium complexity    (C < 10000)│ ~75%
       | Higher analysis
     │ ~25%            │
       │ Difficult complexity (C > 10000)│ ~85%
       | Mostly analysis
     │ ~15%            │
       └────────────────────────┴─────────────────
     ┴─────────────────┘


     STEP 3: APPLY MASTER FORMULA
     ────────────────────────────

       ╔══════════════════════════════════════════
     ═════════════════╗
       ║
                      ║
       ║    a_optimal(C) = W_eff × (1 - 1/ln(C +
     e))              ║
       ║
                      ║
       ╚══════════════════════════════════════════
     ═════════════════╝

       Where:
         a_optimal = processing power used to calculate C = ALLOCATION
     BEFORE outputting
         W_eff     = effective working memory ( CAPPED 80% )
         C         = complexity score
         e         = Euler's number (~2.718)
         ln        = natural logarithm

